Because this is what love is. Love is not breathlessness. It is not excitement. It is not the promulgation of promises of eternal passion. That is just being “in love,” which any of us can convince ourselves we are. Love itself is what is left over when being in love has burned away, and this is both an art and a fortunate accident. Those that truly love... have roots that grow towards each other underground, and when all the pretty blossoms had fallen from their branches they find that they are one tree and not two.” Love is a reaction, a process, where the simpler passions of desire and pleasure are purified and reduced by the growing intimacy and knowingness of each other its fundamental elements, a kind of iconic spiritual purity.

I have nothing but gratitude for everyone I had the absolute privilege to work with in 2022. It was hands down the best year ever! I wish you all love, good health, success (however you define it) peace and prosperity. 2023 is going to be an exciting year. Let’s get it!

Well, here we are. The end of the 2022. We made it to another year. One thought that I keep ingraining in my head is that: If we just keep on moving forward, putting one foot in front of the other, we’re going to be alright.  So,,, here we go - 2023. 

I would like to leave you with this: 

To all the days here and after, may they be filled with fond memories, happiness and laughter. 

May the best day of your past be the worst day of your future. 

May your troubles be less, and your blessings be more. 
And nothing but happiness come through your door. 

May you live as long as you want and never want as long as you live. 

May we all be alive at this same time next year.  And just in case the heavens call your number,,, may you be in heaven a full half hour before the devil knows you're dead. 

Happy New Year!

Three years ago around this time I thought I would never work again, that I am going to lose my house and that we are all going to die. 

Three years later I am traveling all over the country, shooting luxury weddings, and turning down work because I am so busy.

Life. 

Adversity. 

They humble you. They teach you. They build you. 

It’s all an opportunity.

There’s truth to the saying: what doesn’t kill you makes you stronger. 

Everything is going to be alright. Everything is going to work out like they are meant to be. You just have to keep pushing forward. Everyday. Forward. Forward. Forward. Even if it’s just getting up and making your bed and taking a shower. Move. Forward.

Yesterday at the Santa Barbara courthouse Alice and Dane got married. They asked me to be their witness and I of course said yes! I’d be honored to. It was my first witness gig :) 

It was very special. 

And today is the big day. 

Blessed and honored to be here in Santa Ynez valley, California is an understatement, documenting the little and big moments for Alice and Dane. 

Like how?

How do I get to be so blessed with such a wonderful life… filled with joy and love and wonderful people. 

So very grateful….

🖤🖤

Love. 

Connection.

And the people that matter the most.

Family. Friends. Community. 

Good Food. Wine. Meaningful conversations. 

Eloquent and minimal, but timeless.

My team and I - our hearts are full. We are filled with gratitude to be chosen and play a part in immortalizing these memories for Alice and Dane at the most beautiful place to marry- Santa Ynez Valley.

Tomorrow is going to be super special.

A week ago I had the privilege to document Sarah and Mike’s wedding weekend in Pinehurst, North Carolina. 

This morning I said a quick prayer expressing my gratitude to the life I am blessed with. I am blessed with wonderful and kind people to work with day in and day out. I am blessed with people who schedule their wedding celebration around my availability. 

Sarah is the sweetest and kindest person I have ever met. Mike is a wonderful man and they are the perfect fit for each other.  Their love and respect for each other is very encouraging and very inspiring. They have a wonderful support system and I could not be more grateful that I was chosen to document their memories with their closest friends and family. 

Thank you Sarah for planning my wedding around my schedule. I am so happy that our paths crossed. Thank you for choosing me among the sea of talents. 🖤

Thank you Nicole and Lindsay with @visioneventsnc for your commitment and hard work and all of the wedding creative partners for planning along and executing this special weekend. It was the best weekend ever.
The Night Before In Nantucket.

Blue hour… 

Alex called me Thursday morning and said: 

Hey Virgil, it’s going to rain Saturday. And that’s ok. We’ll have magical rainy pictures then too… But it’s nice today. What do you think about taking some pictures of us  this afternoon at sunset? We’ll put on our wedding outfits. 

I’m game. Let’s do it!  I’m there!

Bailey did her hair and makeup and off we went… and it was nothing short of magical. 

I love how my 2023 continue to experience a lot of “firsts.” I love how my couples are more and more choosing a more relaxed and in the moment approach to a lot of things weddings. Less traditional. Less pre-conceived notion of what weddings should be… but choosing to err on more meaningful approach. I love how they just trust and live to the fullest…  and I love how they just value what matters most…

All’s well that end well to end up with you … 

Great friends, closed, tight knit, kind people, dodging rain while enjoying great food and drinks, 3 outfit changes on a lovely place to marry,,, ladies and gentlemen, The Peats.

I say this often,,, the bride and groom’s energy dictates the vibe and energy of the whole wedding weekend.  It starts with you….

Cassidy and Max started the weekend off with just the best attitude and best vibe, stemming from pure joy coming from within, love and gratitude.  I could just feel their amazing energy the moment I met them the night before at their rehearsal dinner. Their friends and family gathered and they were all just so happy- happy to be there, happy to be all together in one place. 

I love that.

That’s what a wedding is about. That’s what every wedding should be about.

Gratitude. 
Joy.
Abundance.
Togetherness.
Conversations. 
Family.
Love.
Tight hugs.
Martinis.
Flowers.
Candles.
A good meal.
Grandpas. 
Drinks flowing.
And lots of dancing, like no one is else is watching. 

I consider it a great privilege to be the one to capture it all. I have so much gratitude for @lizgcole_ for recommending me and for Cassidy for choosing me. Thank you, endlessly. I hope my pictures do all of the beauty justice….

When I was taking photographs of Elle and Foster, I just did my thing and didnt think much of it other than I am documenting love and this present time. I love movement. My blurry” photographs are often caused by movement. They are unintentional and they are seldom planned or “created.” They are often manifestations of my emotions and my excitement while quickly grasping one of my 8 cameras and shooting from the hip. It’s magic. It’s a gift. When I get excited about a moment unfolding in front of me, blur happens. Can’t speak for every photographer out there trying to create their own art. But I have had a lot of requests to include or if I do “blurry pictures” … “it” will happen,,, several times throughout the day. I just don’t know when… but I am here, ready for it.

Life will give you whatever experience is most helpful for the evolution of your consciousness. How do you know this is the experience you need? Because this is the experience you are having at the moment. My favorite quote from Eckhart Toile. 

We don’t know why things or events are happening to us or why people come to our lives. Some stay for a while. Some go eventually. By circumstances or by choice. But *it* happened because it is a part of our growth. The experience was a part of our evolution to ultimately do great things. 

Nantucket, Santa Ynez Valley, New York City, Dallas, Austin, Pinehurst, Atlanta, Charlotte, The Biltmore, Greenville, Columbia, Pawleys Island, Hilton Head Island, Kiawah Island, Charleston. 2023- you have been SOOOO good to us. Nantucket.
It’s a special place.

Sometimes- weddings today are a lot of stress to some.

Some choose to have a 500 person wedding. Some choose to have 150. Some choose to go to the courthouse. And some choose to do it at the Las Vegas chapel with Elvis. And his cat.

Some choose to get married on their hotel balcony, straight out of bed, with their robes on with a couple of friends who also rolled out of bed and didnt brush their teeth at 7:30 am, while the storm is brewing. 

Some get married on their mom and dad’s dock overlooking the marshes and waterways of the Hammock Coast Lowcountry. 

With 12 people.

Like Hannah and Will. 

All are equally unique and equally special. And meaningful. And I am there for it. 

I am grateful to be invited. 

Be blessed.
